WEBVTT

00:02.877 --> 00:05.338
♪

00:05.338 --> 00:06.548
Magnum:
<i>My name is Thomas Magnum.</i>

00:06.548 --> 00:08.174
<i>When I'm not inspiring books</i>

00:08.174 --> 00:09.634
<i>by best-selling author
Robin Masters,</i>

00:09.634 --> 00:11.344
<i>I'm his live-in
security consultant</i>

00:11.344 --> 00:13.847
<i>and a private investigator
in Hawaii.</i>

00:13.847 --> 00:15.223
<i>My buddies and I moved here</i>

00:15.223 --> 00:16.850
<i>after serving together
in Afghanistan,</i>

00:16.850 --> 00:19.352
<i>where we spent time
in a POW camp before escaping.</i>

00:19.352 --> 00:21.104
Make a hell of a team.
<i>That's Rick.</i>

00:21.104 --> 00:23.481
<i>If you want something on the
island, Rick is the man to see.</i>

00:23.481 --> 00:25.108
Hey, what about me?
<i>That's TC.</i>

00:25.108 --> 00:28.194
<i>He runs the best helicopter
tour business on Oahu.</i>

00:28.194 --> 00:29.446
<i>I've also made
some friends here.</i>

00:29.446 --> 00:30.864
Let me see
that Kardashian butt.

00:30.864 --> 00:32.365
<i>This is Kumu.</i>

00:32.365 --> 00:34.325
<i>She's the cultural curator
of Robin's estate.</i>

00:34.325 --> 00:35.869
Detective Katsumoto, HPD.

00:35.869 --> 00:37.287
<i>Make that</i> former <i>HPD.</i>

00:37.287 --> 00:38.663
<i>He recently lost his badge</i>

00:38.663 --> 00:40.415
<i>after he broke a convict
out of prison</i>

00:40.415 --> 00:42.500
<i>in order to save his ex-wife.</i>

00:42.500 --> 00:43.918
Ah! Higgins!

00:43.918 --> 00:45.795
<i>And this is Juliet Higgins,</i>

00:45.795 --> 00:48.048
<i>former British Intelligence, MI6.</i>

00:48.048 --> 00:49.632
<i>She also works for Robin.</i>

00:49.632 --> 00:51.926
You're his major... dodo.

00:51.926 --> 00:53.595
Majordomo.

00:53.595 --> 00:55.138
<i>Sure, we got off
on the wrong foot...</i>

00:55.138 --> 00:57.223
Higgins: Magnum is
an uncultured man-child,

00:57.223 --> 00:59.351
a lazy freeloader,
a terrible driver,

00:59.351 --> 01:01.019
but he is definitely
not a killer.

01:01.019 --> 01:02.228
<i>...but she came around.</i>

01:02.228 --> 01:04.606
We work really well together.

01:05.648 --> 01:06.733
Man: Oh, no!

01:08.151 --> 01:10.278
Magnum, are you about to ask me
to become your partner?

01:10.278 --> 01:12.572
<i>After becoming partners,
we got much closer.</i>

01:12.572 --> 01:14.407
You're my best friend. Ditto.

01:14.407 --> 01:16.034
<i>And then things
got complicated.</i>

01:16.034 --> 01:19.496
You may have said my name
in your sleep last night.

01:19.496 --> 01:21.831
Fine.
I had a dream about you.

01:21.831 --> 01:23.500
A sexy dream.

01:24.751 --> 01:27.921
<i>I may, possibly,
have feelings for Higgins.</i>

01:27.921 --> 01:33.134
I came to tell you
that I have feelings for you.

01:33.134 --> 01:43.103
♪

01:43.103 --> 01:44.688
♪ Outside ♪

01:44.688 --> 01:48.608
♪ My guy is trying to find
a little spare time ♪

01:48.608 --> 01:51.027
♪ Unwind with me a little ♪

01:51.027 --> 01:52.612
♪ I've got red wine ♪

01:52.612 --> 01:56.241
♪ No lie,
and since there's two of us ♪

01:56.241 --> 01:57.617
<i>Living in Hawaii, you find</i>

01:57.617 --> 01:59.327
<i>that each day
is like the one before,</i>

01:59.327 --> 02:03.164
<i>because here, it's always
80 degrees, it's always sunny,</i>

02:03.164 --> 02:06.126
<i>and everywhere you go,
you can feel that Aloha Spirit.</i>

02:06.126 --> 02:09.587
<i>But sometimes, you wake up,
and everything seems different.</i>

02:09.587 --> 02:12.298
<i>Like it's not just gonna be
another day in paradise.</i>

02:12.298 --> 02:14.092
<i>It might even be
something better.</i>

02:14.092 --> 02:18.054
♪ I heard you wanna be
in the driver's seat ♪

02:18.054 --> 02:19.931
Hey.

02:19.931 --> 02:21.057
Hey, yourself.

02:21.057 --> 02:23.893
♪ ...it feels right ♪

02:23.893 --> 02:25.979
<i>Yeah, I know
what you're thinking.</i>

02:25.979 --> 02:28.982
<i>But trust me,
this isn't a dream.</i>

02:28.982 --> 02:30.525
<i>This is really happening.</i>

02:30.525 --> 02:32.402
Thanks for not waking me.

02:32.402 --> 02:36.156
Well, we didn't get
much sleep last night.

02:36.156 --> 02:37.699
Figured you might be tired. Yeah.

02:37.699 --> 02:43.121
We also didn't get a chance
to talk-- about us.

02:43.121 --> 02:44.581
Well, who's fault is that?

02:44.581 --> 02:46.416
I mean, I tried to talk
to you

02:46.416 --> 02:48.835
when we got back
from the hospital, but...

02:48.835 --> 02:50.170
you had other plans.

02:50.170 --> 02:52.505
Are you implying
that I came onto you?

02:52.505 --> 02:54.007
Because that is not
what happened.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.467
That's exactly
what happened.

02:55.467 --> 02:58.511
Okay, well, that is--
That is what happened.

02:58.511 --> 03:00.180
Yeah.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.265
Either way,
we need to talk.

03:02.265 --> 03:04.059
♪ But it feels right ♪

03:04.059 --> 03:06.019
♪ And just the thought of you ♪

03:06.019 --> 03:09.564
♪ Gives me the taste
I know I'll crave ♪

03:09.564 --> 03:12.108
♪ But it feels right ♪

03:12.108 --> 03:15.820
I mean, it's not just that we'd
be jeopardizing our partnership.

03:15.820 --> 03:17.322
Then what is it?

03:17.322 --> 03:19.783
Well, on paper, we really
don't make sense.

03:19.783 --> 03:23.495
The notion that opposites
attract is a total myth.

03:23.495 --> 03:26.373
Our personalities
are vastly different,

03:26.373 --> 03:28.875
and we disagree
on pretty much everything.

03:28.875 --> 03:30.210
Well, on the plus side,

03:30.210 --> 03:31.795
at least now when
we have an issue,

03:31.795 --> 03:35.006
we can resolve those differences
with make-up sex.

03:35.006 --> 03:37.467
Magnum, focus.
[ Chuckles ]

03:37.467 --> 03:42.389
This-- you and me--
it's-- it's inherently risky.

03:42.389 --> 03:45.350
Yeah, but most things
that are worth it are.

03:45.350 --> 03:48.770
But I'm willing to give it
a chance.

03:51.898 --> 03:53.316
Then so am I.

03:53.316 --> 04:00.323
♪

04:00.323 --> 04:01.574
But, you know,
I-I would like

04:01.574 --> 04:03.493
to just set out
a few ground rules.

04:03.493 --> 04:05.286
Okay, here we go.

04:05.286 --> 04:06.496
Well,
what does that mean?

04:06.496 --> 04:07.956
It's just so you.

04:07.956 --> 04:10.125
You want to set rules and--
and-- and boundaries and...

04:10.125 --> 04:12.752
No, no, no. Just--
Just hear me out, would you?

04:12.752 --> 04:14.087
I'm not sure
that you're aware of this,

04:14.087 --> 04:17.549
but our friends are actually
kind of invested

04:17.549 --> 04:19.467
in the idea of you
and me as a couple.

04:19.467 --> 04:20.719
Oh, I'm aware.

04:20.719 --> 04:23.888
They even have a text chain
about it.

04:23.888 --> 04:25.598
That's kind of juvenile.

04:25.598 --> 04:26.975
But, anyway, look,
we need

04:26.975 --> 04:29.436
to give each other time
to figure this out.

04:29.436 --> 04:33.606
We don't need other people
influencing us.

04:33.606 --> 04:36.276
So, you want to keep it
on the DL.

04:36.276 --> 04:39.112
Precisely.
[ Knock on door ]

04:39.112 --> 04:40.447
Kumu: Thomas, you up?

04:40.447 --> 04:41.698
On that note,
you better hide.

04:41.698 --> 04:42.782
No, this is my house.
<i>You</i> hide.

04:42.782 --> 04:43.950
It's Robin's house.
Really?

04:43.950 --> 04:45.285
We're gonna do
this right now?

04:45.285 --> 04:46.453
Come on.
Get in the kitchen.

04:46.453 --> 04:48.621
[ Clears throat ]

04:48.621 --> 04:50.540
Hey, Kumu.
What's up?

04:50.540 --> 04:51.583
Have you seen Juliet?

04:51.583 --> 04:53.126
She's not in the main house.

04:53.126 --> 04:55.837
No,
she's probably riding.

04:55.837 --> 04:58.923
Well, that's what I thought,
but her horse is in the stable.

04:58.923 --> 05:02.052
Did you try
the wine cellar?

05:02.052 --> 05:05.221
Why would she be in the wine
cellar at 7:30 in the morning?

05:05.221 --> 05:06.639
Oh.
She didn't tell you?

05:06.639 --> 05:09.267
No, no, Higgy is on this whole
"rise and wine" kick.

05:09.267 --> 05:11.478
Claims there are health benefits
to drinking in the morning.

05:11.478 --> 05:12.687
Personally,
I think she just--

05:12.687 --> 05:14.564
She just wants
to hit the bottle.

05:14.564 --> 05:16.983
Okay.
I'll check the cellar. Yeah.

05:16.983 --> 05:19.319
Oh, a-and you got a call
on the house line

05:19.319 --> 05:20.487
just a few minutes ago.

05:20.487 --> 05:21.613
New client. Okay.

05:21.613 --> 05:23.114
She's on her way.

05:23.114 --> 05:25.033
I will get dressed ASAP.

05:26.201 --> 05:27.494
[ Door closes ]

05:27.494 --> 05:28.661
"Rise and wine"?

05:28.661 --> 05:30.872
I got rid of her,
didn't I?

05:30.872 --> 05:32.665
And, besides, I don't
really like the idea

05:32.665 --> 05:34.125
of lying to our friends.

05:34.125 --> 05:36.378
I-I mean, lying to Katsumoto
is okay because I kind of--

05:36.378 --> 05:37.921
You do it all the time?
Precisely.

05:37.921 --> 05:41.216
But Rick and Kumu and TC,
it just feels...

05:41.216 --> 05:42.550
wrong.

05:42.550 --> 05:46.888
Look, it doesn't make me
feel good, either.

05:46.888 --> 05:49.599
But I think that we owe it
to ourselves

05:49.599 --> 05:53.603
to give this
a real chance of success.

05:53.603 --> 05:55.772
Moreover, if it doesn't
work out,

05:55.772 --> 05:58.191
it's just gonna be harder
if everyone knows.

05:58.191 --> 06:00.193
Yeah, that's a good point.

06:00.193 --> 06:01.861
And...

06:01.861 --> 06:05.365
sneaking around
might be kind of fun,

06:05.365 --> 06:08.910
in a naughty way.

06:08.910 --> 06:10.829
That's
an even better point.

06:10.829 --> 06:19.504
♪

06:19.504 --> 06:21.172
So, how you doing, man?

06:21.172 --> 06:24.592
Aside from suddenly
being unemployed, I'm good.

06:24.592 --> 06:26.052
So, what happens now?

06:26.052 --> 06:28.388
I mean, they just can't
take your badge, right?

06:28.388 --> 06:30.682
No, they can.

06:30.682 --> 06:33.810
Unless I decide to fight it,
which I'm not going to.

06:33.810 --> 06:35.311
Wait, why the hell not?

06:35.311 --> 06:36.730
'Cause I knew
what I was doing,

06:36.730 --> 06:39.232
and I'm prepared
to accept the consequences.

06:39.232 --> 06:40.692
You sure, Gordie?

06:40.692 --> 06:44.237
You really just wanna give up
that easy?

06:44.237 --> 06:46.573
I've made my peace with it.

06:46.573 --> 06:48.158
Of course now, I have
to figure out my next move.

06:48.158 --> 06:51.911
I never imagined I'd be 45
and starting over,

06:51.911 --> 06:52.954
but here I am.

06:52.954 --> 06:55.081
Yeah, I know what
that feels like.

06:55.081 --> 06:56.875
So do Thomas, Rick,
and Higgy.

06:56.875 --> 06:58.918
But you'll figure it out
like we did.

07:01.296 --> 07:03.381
In the meantime, you know
I got your back, right?

07:03.381 --> 07:04.632
I do.

07:04.632 --> 07:06.009
You're also picking up
the check, I hope,

07:06.009 --> 07:07.635
'cause who knows
when I'll have a job again.

07:07.635 --> 07:09.554
Oh, man, you know...

07:09.554 --> 07:10.638
my wallet
fell out the chopper.

07:10.638 --> 07:11.598
Mm. Got it.

07:11.598 --> 07:13.308
No, I got you, man.

07:13.308 --> 07:14.684
[ Both laugh ]

07:16.519 --> 07:19.439
I've been going back
and forth on this.

07:19.439 --> 07:24.194
I want answers, but I'm also
afraid of what I might learn.

07:24.194 --> 07:27.280
You're definitely not the first
client to feel that way,

07:27.280 --> 07:31.451
but why don't we just start
with what brought you here?

07:31.451 --> 07:35.121
Six nights ago...

07:35.121 --> 07:38.249
my husband, Greg,
died in a car accident.

07:38.249 --> 07:39.668
It was late.

07:39.668 --> 07:42.837
He was driving home from work
and took a turn too fast

07:42.837 --> 07:45.882
and slammed into a divider.

07:45.882 --> 07:47.550
So sorry.

07:47.550 --> 07:51.388
Paramedics said
he was killed instantly.

07:51.388 --> 07:53.139
No one saw anything.

07:53.139 --> 07:58.019
But yesterday, I went to
the mailbox and...

07:59.646 --> 08:01.648
...found this.

08:01.648 --> 08:03.274
It's a red light
camera ticket.

08:03.274 --> 08:06.861
That photo was taken less than
two minutes before the crash.

08:06.861 --> 08:09.781
But as you can see--
He's clearly not alone.

08:09.781 --> 08:11.324
There's someone
in the passenger seat.

08:11.324 --> 08:13.910
The police said there was
no one else in the vehicle,

08:13.910 --> 08:18.873
so I don't know
if she survived and ran off

08:18.873 --> 08:21.835
or if Greg let her out
before he crashed.

08:21.835 --> 08:24.462
I take it you don't know
who this is?

08:24.462 --> 08:26.131
No.

08:26.131 --> 08:27.340
That's why I'm here.

08:27.340 --> 08:31.511
Greg is-- was--

08:31.511 --> 08:32.929
the last person

08:32.929 --> 08:35.181
I'd suspect
of having an affair.

08:35.181 --> 08:36.850
He was a good man.

08:36.850 --> 08:40.228
But maybe there was
another side to him.

08:42.564 --> 08:43.982
The resolution
on this photo

08:43.982 --> 08:45.942
is too poor
for facial recognition,

08:45.942 --> 08:48.570
but we can definitely
look into it,

08:48.570 --> 08:50.947
if that's what you want.

08:50.947 --> 08:52.115
[ Sighs ]

08:52.115 --> 08:54.075
It is.

08:54.075 --> 08:58.371
I have to know the truth.
For my own peace of mind.

08:58.371 --> 08:59.831
I need answers.

08:59.831 --> 09:02.250
We'll do everything we can
to get you some.

09:02.250 --> 09:22.270
♪

09:22.270 --> 09:24.522
[ Cellphone rings ]

09:24.522 --> 09:25.732
[ Cellphone beeps ]

09:25.732 --> 09:27.067
Rick:
<i>What do you need, Thomas?</i>

09:27.067 --> 09:28.443
I'll tell you what
I don't need--

09:28.443 --> 09:30.570
an eyeful
of ear wax and hair.

09:30.570 --> 09:31.654
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

09:31.654 --> 09:33.073
You're on FaceTime, pal.

09:33.073 --> 09:34.240
<i>Ah. Sorry.</i>

09:34.240 --> 09:35.575
There she is.

09:35.575 --> 09:37.452
Look at
that little ball of Joy.

09:37.452 --> 09:39.120
Wait, why--
why are you naked?

09:39.120 --> 09:40.955
I'm not naked.
We're bonding here, okay?

09:40.955 --> 09:42.749
This is called Skin to Skin.

09:42.749 --> 09:45.210
My heartbeat calms the baby,
and this way,

09:45.210 --> 09:47.170
she learns my scent.

09:47.170 --> 09:48.296
She is too cute.

09:48.296 --> 09:49.923
Hey, hey, Rick, listen,
I need a favor.

09:49.923 --> 09:51.549
<i>Of course you do.</i>

09:51.549 --> 09:53.510
<i>You know, Thomas, this is
getting really tiresome.</i>

09:53.510 --> 09:55.679
<i>You know what kind of
friendship they call this?</i>

09:55.679 --> 09:56.763
<i>Transactional.</i>

09:56.763 --> 09:57.931
<i>And it's toxic.</i>

09:57.931 --> 10:00.266
[ Sighs ]
Someone's a little cranky.

10:00.266 --> 10:01.935
Uh, let's see.
I have a newborn,

10:01.935 --> 10:03.770
I got 20 minutes of sleep
last night,

10:03.770 --> 10:05.522
I got to cover the bar
in an hour,

10:05.522 --> 10:06.898
I forgot to buy a car seat,

10:06.898 --> 10:08.775
and I'm closing on my new house
this week.

10:08.775 --> 10:10.443
Alright, sounds like
you got a full plate.

10:10.443 --> 10:11.903
I'll tell you what,

10:11.903 --> 10:13.738
I'll take one
of those things off your list.

10:13.738 --> 10:16.491
You'll be Joy's dad
so I can get some sleep?

10:16.491 --> 10:17.992
No, I was thinking
the car seat.

10:17.992 --> 10:20.578
Oh.
That-- That would be helpful.

10:20.578 --> 10:23.206
Thank you.
<i>No problem.</i>

10:23.206 --> 10:26.001
<i>Okay, now is
where you ask me,</i>

10:26.001 --> 10:27.460
<i>"What was that favor
you needed?"</i>

10:27.460 --> 10:29.170
<i>And I tell you, "Can you
reach out to your guy</i>

10:29.170 --> 10:30.964
<i>at the Department
of Transportation</i>

10:30.964 --> 10:32.424
<i>to pull some traffic cam
footage?"</i>

10:32.424 --> 10:34.592
<i>And I'm also gonna need you
to track down</i>

10:34.592 --> 10:36.469
<i>a BMW X5 that's totaled.</i>

10:36.469 --> 10:38.847
<i>Uh, it's probably
at an impound lot.</i>

10:38.847 --> 10:40.515
<i>I just have no idea
which one, though.</i>

10:40.515 --> 10:42.142
Okay,
let me get this straight.

10:42.142 --> 10:44.310
You take one thing off my to-do
list and you add two more.

10:44.310 --> 10:47.397
<i>Come on, Rick.
It's a couple phone calls.</i>

10:47.397 --> 10:49.649
<i>Please?</i>

10:49.649 --> 10:50.775
Okay.

10:50.775 --> 10:52.277
Send over the details.

10:52.277 --> 10:53.528
<i>Thank you.</i>

10:53.528 --> 10:56.489
And, hey, don't cheap out
on that car seat.

10:56.489 --> 10:58.283
Wouldn't dream of it.

10:58.283 --> 11:01.578
♪

11:01.578 --> 11:04.748
Higgins: Alright, first stop--
Dr. Macy's office.

11:04.748 --> 11:07.667
♪

11:07.667 --> 11:09.836
[ Doorbell rings ]

11:09.836 --> 11:18.970
♪

11:18.970 --> 11:21.806
[ Lock disengages ]

11:21.806 --> 11:23.683
[ Bell ringing ]

11:23.683 --> 11:53.463
♪

11:53.463 --> 11:55.757
[ Telephone beeps ]

11:55.757 --> 11:57.050
Looks like the day he died,

11:57.050 --> 11:58.468
Macy placed two calls

11:58.468 --> 11:59.969
to Hadley & Kroy.

11:59.969 --> 12:02.180
That's the island's
top divorce firm.

12:02.180 --> 12:04.391
Yeah.
It's not a good sign.

12:04.391 --> 12:05.725
And it gets worse.

12:05.725 --> 12:06.893
Dr. Macy was researching

12:06.893 --> 12:09.062
temporary housing
in Kapolei,

12:09.062 --> 12:10.897
and he'd had recently downloaded
a third-party

12:10.897 --> 12:13.483
messaging app that allows
for covert communication.

12:13.483 --> 12:14.734
Blind Message?
Mm-hmm.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.903
That's the go-to app
for serial cheaters.

12:16.903 --> 12:18.738
Yeah.
Can you access the account?

12:18.738 --> 12:20.365
Yeah.

12:20.365 --> 12:22.117
Looks like Dr. Macy
was chatting with somebody

12:22.117 --> 12:24.077
who goes by the letter "J."

12:24.077 --> 12:25.870
How bad are the messages?

12:25.870 --> 12:27.205
Well, in the last one,
Dr. Macy

12:27.205 --> 12:29.416
says, "How are you?
I'm thinking about you."

12:29.416 --> 12:32.293
To which J responds,
"I can't talk.

12:32.293 --> 12:33.420
He's home."

12:33.420 --> 12:36.047
Looks like Sara's fears
were justified.

12:36.047 --> 12:37.882
We have to find out who
this J person is.

12:37.882 --> 12:39.509
[ Bell ringing ]

12:39.509 --> 12:45.640
♪

12:45.640 --> 12:46.766
Aloha.

12:46.766 --> 12:48.810
Sorry.
Clinic's closed.

12:48.810 --> 12:50.687
You don't look like doctors.

12:50.687 --> 12:52.439
[ American accent ]
We're not.

12:52.439 --> 12:53.940
HPD.

12:53.940 --> 12:56.151
I'm afraid you're gonna have
to go elsewhere, sir.

12:57.318 --> 12:58.570
Hmm.

12:58.570 --> 12:59.779
I've got one of those, too.

12:59.779 --> 13:00.822
Except mine's real.

13:00.822 --> 13:03.366
♪

13:08.747 --> 13:10.957
[ Sighs ]
I told you one of these days,

13:10.957 --> 13:13.835
those badges were gonna
get us into trouble.

13:13.835 --> 13:15.962
Yeah, and you were right.

13:15.962 --> 13:18.506
Wait, what?
Well, you did warn me.

13:18.506 --> 13:22.260
Are you-- Are you just being
placatory because we're now...

13:22.260 --> 13:24.137
You are, aren't you?

13:24.137 --> 13:25.722
Maybe a little bit.
Please don't.

13:25.722 --> 13:27.682
Could you just be yourself?

13:29.517 --> 13:31.269
Okay, let's talk about
what you two are doing here.

13:31.269 --> 13:35.106
Well, Macy's wife hired us
to investigate his death.

13:35.106 --> 13:37.400
Why would she hire
a couple of private eyes?

13:37.400 --> 13:38.902
Investigators.
Investigators.

13:38.902 --> 13:40.278
Macy died
in a car accident.

13:40.278 --> 13:41.654
There was nothing suspicious
about it,

13:41.654 --> 13:44.407
and yet, here you are,
searching his office.

13:44.407 --> 13:45.617
Why?

13:45.617 --> 13:47.869
Well, it was at least
a little suspicious.

13:47.869 --> 13:49.162
He was an impeccable driver,

13:49.162 --> 13:50.663
he had no moving violations.

13:50.663 --> 13:51.831
Was he upset?

13:51.831 --> 13:54.000
Did he get into
some kind of altercation?

13:54.000 --> 13:56.169
His wife just wants answers.

13:56.169 --> 13:58.838
Detective, if I may,
why are <i>you</i> here?

13:58.838 --> 14:01.675
I mean, a car accident is kind
of below your pay grade, no?

14:01.675 --> 14:03.510
I just transferred into Central
this morning,

14:03.510 --> 14:05.011
and I heard a couple
of PIs requested

14:05.011 --> 14:06.304
Macy's accident report,

14:06.304 --> 14:09.516
and I just thought
that was a little... odd.

14:09.516 --> 14:11.351
I figured this might be
your next stop.

14:11.351 --> 14:13.978
You know, they warned me
about you two already.

14:13.978 --> 14:16.064
It seems your reputations
precede you.

14:16.064 --> 14:18.191
Can't tell if that
was an insult.

14:18.191 --> 14:19.693
It wasn't a compliment.

14:19.693 --> 14:20.902
Mm.

14:20.902 --> 14:21.903
So, will
you be charging us?

14:21.903 --> 14:24.030
I haven't decided yet.

14:24.030 --> 14:25.365
He will not be charging us.

14:25.365 --> 14:26.574
Oh, no?
No.

14:26.574 --> 14:28.827
I'm guessing
you're Robbery-Homicide.

14:28.827 --> 14:30.704
Yeah, you got to do
all this paperwork,

14:30.704 --> 14:33.373
a full day in court
for, what, a misdemeanor.

14:33.373 --> 14:34.833
That's not gonna happen.

14:34.833 --> 14:37.544
Hmm. Your boyfriend
brings up a good point.

14:37.544 --> 14:39.212
We're not--
No, no. We're not involved.

14:39.212 --> 14:41.131
No.
Hands.

14:43.383 --> 14:46.219
So, this is your first
and only warning.

14:46.219 --> 14:47.387
Get involved
in the case again,

14:47.387 --> 14:49.222
you'll see
the inside of a cell.

14:49.222 --> 14:53.393
Well, very nice to meet you, Detective.

14:53.393 --> 14:55.729
That must be
Gordon's replacement.

14:55.729 --> 14:57.230
Yeah.

14:57.230 --> 14:59.733
You lied to him
about Macy's companion.

14:59.733 --> 15:02.777
Well, Sara did ask us
to use discretion, right?

15:02.777 --> 15:05.113
[ Cellphone rings ]

15:05.113 --> 15:07.449
Thomas Magnum.
Lee: Lieutenant Magnum,

15:07.449 --> 15:09.576
this is Commander Rachel Lee
over at Pearl.

15:09.576 --> 15:10.952
I was hoping you could tell me

15:10.952 --> 15:12.954
how to get in contact
with Captain Buck Greene.

15:12.954 --> 15:16.082
I've been trying, but his phone
is no longer in service.

15:16.082 --> 15:18.084
Uh, Captain Greene?

15:18.084 --> 15:20.086
No, I'm sorry.
I can't.

15:20.086 --> 15:22.047
Oh, that's odd.
You're listed in his file

15:22.047 --> 15:23.548
as the emergency contact.

15:23.548 --> 15:26.092
Well, that's news to me.
I haven't spoken to Greene

15:26.092 --> 15:28.595
but maybe once
in the past three years.

15:28.595 --> 15:30.597
Yeah.
What is this about?

15:30.597 --> 15:32.932
Well, sir, Captain Greene
hasn't cashed

15:32.932 --> 15:34.601
his pension check in weeks.

15:34.601 --> 15:37.479
His last known address
is a PO box in Haleiwa,

15:37.479 --> 15:39.397
but he hasn't emptied it
in a while,

15:39.397 --> 15:41.024
so I've been trying
to track him down.

15:41.024 --> 15:43.568
I'm sorry. I wish I could help,
but I don't have any info.

15:43.568 --> 15:45.862
Understood.
I appreciate your time, sir.

15:45.862 --> 15:47.280
Good day.

15:47.280 --> 15:49.866
Apparently, Greene
dropped off the grid.

15:49.866 --> 15:51.117
That's odd.

15:51.117 --> 15:52.786
Also odd
that your former C.O.,

15:52.786 --> 15:55.330
who betrayed you
and nearly got you killed,

15:55.330 --> 15:58.333
then lists you as
his emergency contact.

16:00.168 --> 16:01.670
Yeah.

16:01.670 --> 16:07.634
♪

16:07.634 --> 16:10.345
Ooh.
What is going on here?

16:10.345 --> 16:13.181
With Joy coming early,
Rick didn't have a chance

16:13.181 --> 16:14.724
to schedule
any paternity leave,

16:14.724 --> 16:17.811
so he needed someone to come
in and sling Mai Tais.

16:17.811 --> 16:20.939
Lucky for him, I bartended
my way through grad school

16:20.939 --> 16:23.692
in the '7-- '80s.
Right.

16:23.692 --> 16:25.568
Oh, look at this.

16:25.568 --> 16:27.320
- You didn't get the budget model.
- Come on.

16:27.320 --> 16:29.072
We're talking about
my goddaughter here.

16:29.072 --> 16:30.323
Only the best for her.

16:30.323 --> 16:31.908
Yeah, yeah,
you spare no expense.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.159
Thank you, Jules.

16:33.159 --> 16:34.577
I know who paid for that.

16:34.577 --> 16:36.246
Well, you know,
I covered the tax, and that's--

16:36.246 --> 16:37.330
that's really
where they get you.

16:37.330 --> 16:38.665
Yes, he did.

16:38.665 --> 16:40.458
Uh, did you track down
the car yet?

16:40.458 --> 16:41.668
Well, what's left of it.

16:41.668 --> 16:43.503
It's at the impound lot
in Waipahu.

16:43.503 --> 16:44.713
Hmm.
Okay, great.

16:44.713 --> 16:46.798
And what about
the traffic cam footage?

16:46.798 --> 16:48.091
Sorry. One for two.

16:48.091 --> 16:50.719
Mu guy at the DOT
is off-island and unreachable.

16:50.719 --> 16:53.596
Okay. Um, I can take a run
at their firewall.

16:53.596 --> 16:56.808
Or we can ask them
for a professional courtesy.

16:56.808 --> 16:58.226
What?

16:59.310 --> 17:01.312
Aloha.
This is Detective Childs,

17:01.312 --> 17:03.606
badge number 5652.

17:03.606 --> 17:06.109
I was wondering if I can pull
the traffic cam footage

17:06.109 --> 17:08.528
from Cooke and Green,

17:08.528 --> 17:13.116
uh, from around 10:55 p.m.
to 11:00 p.m. last Thursday.

17:13.116 --> 17:14.492
Uh, no, no, it's fine.

17:14.492 --> 17:16.619
Go ahead
and text me a link.

17:16.619 --> 17:19.122
808-555-0121.

17:19.122 --> 17:20.123
Great.

17:20.123 --> 17:21.833
Mahalo.

17:21.833 --> 17:23.626
You memorized
his badge number.

17:23.626 --> 17:27.380
I didn't think
I would need it so soon.

17:27.380 --> 17:28.840
Okay, this is all the coverage
that we have

17:28.840 --> 17:31.551
between the red light
and near where Dr. Macy crashed.

17:31.551 --> 17:34.721
[ Cellphone rings ]

17:34.721 --> 17:36.181
Hey.
You got my message.

17:36.181 --> 17:37.265
Yeah, you sounded worried, TM.

17:37.265 --> 17:38.725
Well, I am.

17:38.725 --> 17:40.226
Yeah, I just want
to make sure Greene's okay,

17:40.226 --> 17:43.229
and we're on a case right now,
so could you help out?

17:43.229 --> 17:44.356
Yeah, I got you.

17:44.356 --> 17:45.857
So, any ideas
where to start?

17:45.857 --> 17:48.234
He did mention having a place
near Anahulu River,

17:48.234 --> 17:50.653
but that's all I got.

17:50.653 --> 17:52.655
Alright, I'll head up there
and ask around.

17:52.655 --> 17:54.449
Alright.
Thanks, TC.

17:55.825 --> 17:59.245
I think it's nice that you want
to look in on Captain Greene.

17:59.245 --> 18:01.623
Well, somebody has to.
I mean, the guy has no one.

18:01.623 --> 18:03.917
After his son got killed,

18:03.917 --> 18:06.753
the Navy was the only family
he had left,

18:06.753 --> 18:09.506
and when he lost
his commission,

18:09.506 --> 18:11.091
he lost everything.

18:11.091 --> 18:13.677
You know what?
It's-- It's not just that.

18:13.677 --> 18:17.097
I mean, outside of my dad and
my uncle, there's really no man

18:17.097 --> 18:19.641
that had more of an impact
on my life than Greene.

18:19.641 --> 18:21.559
He's the one who put
the team together.

18:21.559 --> 18:24.020
You know, me and Rick
and Nuzo and TC.

18:24.020 --> 18:25.397
Two Marines, two SEALs.

18:25.397 --> 18:28.525
That was--
That was his idea.

18:28.525 --> 18:30.026
I'm sure he's fine.

18:30.026 --> 18:34.489
He probably just wanted
to unplug for a couple of weeks

18:34.489 --> 18:36.616
and took a trip
or something.

18:36.616 --> 18:39.285
Yeah, well,
I hope you're right.

18:39.285 --> 18:41.162
So, what do we got?

18:41.162 --> 18:42.539
Well, what we don't have

18:42.539 --> 18:44.624
is a view
of the actual crash, but look.

18:44.624 --> 18:47.085
Here is where Dr. Macy
ran the red light.

18:47.085 --> 18:48.795
It was red for at least
a couple seconds

18:48.795 --> 18:50.505
before he blew through it. Mm.

18:50.505 --> 18:52.632
It doesn't look like
he was just being careless.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.384
Oh, look at that.

18:54.384 --> 18:56.636
Yeah, that SUV
ran the red, as well.

18:56.636 --> 18:58.763
Maybe he was chasing
Dr. Macy.

18:58.763 --> 19:00.473
Well,
we're about to find out.

19:00.473 --> 19:02.308
Hang on.
[ Keyboard clacking ]

19:02.308 --> 19:03.810
Okay.

19:03.810 --> 19:07.147
About two blocks later,
he takes a turn down an alley.

19:07.147 --> 19:09.024
Then he lets her out.

19:10.442 --> 19:14.112
And there's the SUV again.

19:14.112 --> 19:17.032
Okay, unfortunately,
that's where our coverage ends.

19:17.032 --> 19:18.283
But it's clear that that SUV

19:18.283 --> 19:19.617
was in pursuit
of Dr. Macy.

19:19.617 --> 19:21.745
Yeah, and 30 seconds later,
he crashes.

19:21.745 --> 19:25.415
I mean, this-- this doesn't
look like an ordinary accident.

19:25.415 --> 19:26.666
No.

19:26.666 --> 19:28.251
It might be murder.

19:28.251 --> 19:30.587
♪

19:34.924 --> 19:39.429
♪

19:39.429 --> 19:41.264
The SUV pursuing Dr. Macy

19:41.264 --> 19:44.726
is registered to a dummy
corporation in Panama City.

19:44.726 --> 19:46.770
Oh, not suspicious at all. Yeah.

19:46.770 --> 19:48.438
We need to figure out
who was behind the wheel

19:48.438 --> 19:50.065
and whether they were
after Dr. Macy,

19:50.065 --> 19:52.108
his passenger,
or both of them.

19:52.108 --> 19:55.278
Here's another question--
At what point do we loop in HPD?

19:55.278 --> 19:57.322
Well, if we give them
the heads-up now,

19:57.322 --> 19:59.949
our involvement in the case
is basically over.

19:59.949 --> 20:02.702
So I say we wait
until we absolutely can't.

20:02.702 --> 20:16.007
♪

20:16.007 --> 20:17.634
[ Knocking ]

20:17.634 --> 20:21.346
♪

20:21.346 --> 20:23.181
[ Door closes ]

20:23.181 --> 20:53.503
♪

20:53.503 --> 20:56.047
I don't see any evidence
that it was forced off the road

20:56.047 --> 20:57.841
or PIT maneuvered.

20:57.841 --> 20:59.676
Yeah.
Let's look inside.

20:59.676 --> 21:16.526
♪

21:16.526 --> 21:17.736
Nothing up here.

21:17.736 --> 21:19.320
Yeah. Same.

21:20.905 --> 21:24.367
Oh, hang on.

21:24.367 --> 21:25.368
Look at that.

21:25.368 --> 21:27.328
What is that?

21:27.328 --> 21:29.164
A fingernail?
It's an acrylic one.

21:29.164 --> 21:30.790
I don't reckon it belongs
to our client, though.

21:30.790 --> 21:32.083
She didn't have
her nails done.

21:32.083 --> 21:33.543
Maybe it belongs
to our mystery woman.

21:33.543 --> 21:35.128
Right. I mean,
if she was gripping

21:35.128 --> 21:36.629
the dashboard really hard

21:36.629 --> 21:38.465
when they were being chased,
it could have broken off.

21:38.465 --> 21:41.384
I mean,
it's a long shot, but...

21:41.384 --> 21:43.219
it looks like one of Kimee's.
I'm sorry?

21:43.219 --> 21:44.763
There's only a few people
on the island

21:44.763 --> 21:46.389
that do custom nails
like this.

21:46.389 --> 21:48.308
Okay, since when did you become
such an expert

21:48.308 --> 21:49.601
in ladies' fingernails?

21:49.601 --> 21:52.312
Did you date a manicurist
or something?

21:52.312 --> 21:54.397
Two, actually,
and one of them,

21:54.397 --> 21:56.733
Kimee, she would do
custom work like this.

21:56.733 --> 21:58.902
If it's her work,
she might be able to tell us

21:58.902 --> 22:00.236
who it belonged to.

22:00.236 --> 22:01.613
Right.

22:01.613 --> 22:02.822
Okay.

22:02.822 --> 22:08.745
♪

22:08.745 --> 22:10.121
Two, huh?

22:11.456 --> 22:12.916
That doesn't bother you,
does it?

22:12.916 --> 22:14.167
No, no, no.

22:14.167 --> 22:15.585
I'm well aware
that you've had

22:15.585 --> 22:18.672
your fair share of dalliances
over the years.

22:18.672 --> 22:21.091
[ Laughs ] Isn't it kinda weird
that we know so much

22:21.091 --> 22:23.051
about each other's history?

22:23.051 --> 22:24.469
Kind of.

22:24.469 --> 22:26.596
But, I mean, there isn't much
about this situation

22:26.596 --> 22:28.181
that's normal.

22:28.181 --> 22:30.600
I mean, we're practically
living together already.

22:30.600 --> 22:32.769
We didn't even have
a proper courtship.

22:32.769 --> 22:36.106
You never had to pursue me
or romance me.

22:36.106 --> 22:40.068
Most guys would kill for
that arrangement, by the way.

22:40.068 --> 22:42.904
Well, I'm not most guys.

22:42.904 --> 22:45.448
'Cause you're a romantic. Mm.

22:45.448 --> 22:49.035
Well, you know, I actually
think courtship is overrated.

22:49.035 --> 22:51.037
You do?
Yes. I do.

22:51.037 --> 22:53.623
It's two people putting
their best foot forward,

22:53.623 --> 22:55.291
pretending to be something
that they're not.

22:55.291 --> 22:58.086
It's-- It's dishonest.
Come on.

22:58.086 --> 23:01.047
That is--
That is a bit cynical, isn't it?

23:01.047 --> 23:03.383
Maybe.

23:03.383 --> 23:06.052
For what it's worth, I think
I might actually have enjoyed

23:06.052 --> 23:08.054
being courted by you.

23:08.054 --> 23:09.681
Well, I agree.

23:09.681 --> 23:13.309
'Cause my courtship game--
pretty strong.

23:15.061 --> 23:17.981
Of that, I have no doubt.

23:17.981 --> 23:21.985
♪

23:21.985 --> 23:23.945
How's Suzy doing?

23:23.945 --> 23:25.405
Tired.

23:25.405 --> 23:27.532
Yeah, what she went through
must've been scary.

23:27.532 --> 23:28.700
Yeah.

23:30.785 --> 23:33.163
Speaking of bad things
that happened yesterday,

23:33.163 --> 23:35.999
I heard about you and HPD.

23:35.999 --> 23:37.751
You alright?
Hanging in there.

23:37.751 --> 23:39.419
Hm.
Here.

23:42.088 --> 23:45.133
Oh, oh, oh.

23:45.133 --> 23:48.303
TC says you're not
gonna fight this.

23:48.303 --> 23:49.971
Do all of you tell
each other everything,

23:49.971 --> 23:51.514
or do you have,
like, a hive mind?

23:51.514 --> 23:52.849
[ Chuckles ]

23:52.849 --> 23:55.226
No, we have
a text thread.

23:56.561 --> 23:58.188
He was concerned
about you.

23:58.188 --> 24:00.148
So am I.

24:00.148 --> 24:02.692
It just doesn't make
any sense.

24:02.692 --> 24:04.444
I broke a convicted felon
out of prison,

24:04.444 --> 24:06.154
and I refused to give up
my accomplices.

24:06.154 --> 24:07.447
I'd say the punishment
fits the crime.

24:07.447 --> 24:09.699
Well, what choice
did you have?

24:09.699 --> 24:10.700
They took Beth.

24:10.700 --> 24:12.452
You did what you had to do.

24:16.373 --> 24:19.584
Or is there some other reason
why you're not fighting this?

24:23.588 --> 24:25.423
I'm not gonna fight for
something I don't deserve.

24:25.423 --> 24:26.883
Come on.
What are you talking about?

24:26.883 --> 24:29.886
I was gonna shoot
an unarmed man in cold blood.

24:29.886 --> 24:32.889
I came as close as anyone can
to stepping over that line.

24:32.889 --> 24:34.557
Okay. But you didn't.

24:34.557 --> 24:36.434
Only because Magnum stopped me.
Come on.

24:36.434 --> 24:39.229
If you pulled that trigger,
Thomas wasn't gonna turn you in.

24:39.229 --> 24:40.313
You know that.

24:40.313 --> 24:43.233
You stopped yourself, Gordie.

24:43.233 --> 24:44.401
Doesn't feel that way.

24:44.401 --> 24:46.861
Maybe not,
but that's what happened.

24:46.861 --> 24:49.864
Don't punish yourself
for almost making a mistake.

24:49.864 --> 24:52.409
The real mistake would be
for you to roll over

24:52.409 --> 24:55.954
and accept what's happening.

24:55.954 --> 24:57.789
You gotta fight this.

24:57.789 --> 25:01.668
♪

25:06.840 --> 25:08.299
♪

25:08.299 --> 25:10.051
[ Line ringing ]

25:10.051 --> 25:11.886
Kimee: Thomas Magnum.

25:11.886 --> 25:13.805
How's it going, stranger?

25:13.805 --> 25:15.432
Hey, Kimee, how are you?

25:15.432 --> 25:17.142
Well, I'm doing better now.

25:17.142 --> 25:19.728
Look, I'm-- I'm gonna send you
a picture of something, okay?

25:19.728 --> 25:21.896
[ Chuckles ] You know, with
some guys, that usually means

25:21.896 --> 25:23.690
a photo
of a certain appendage

25:23.690 --> 25:25.859
is about to show up
in my in-box...

25:25.859 --> 25:27.736
pardon the pun.

25:27.736 --> 25:29.237
She's normally
not like this.

25:29.237 --> 25:30.822
Oh, I'm sure.

25:30.822 --> 25:33.408
No, seriously, Kimee,
I-I-I need your help, right?

25:33.408 --> 25:34.534
I'm working on a case.

25:34.534 --> 25:35.952
Did you--
Did you get the photo?

25:35.952 --> 25:37.120
Uh, yeah.

25:37.120 --> 25:38.830
It's one of my nails.
Oh, great.

25:38.830 --> 25:41.249
Can you tell me
who it belongs to?

25:41.249 --> 25:43.335
Sure.
Uh, Melinda Parker.

25:43.335 --> 25:44.586
She loved this design.

25:44.586 --> 25:45.837
You got a number for her?

25:45.837 --> 25:47.047
Uh, yeah.

25:47.047 --> 25:48.757
I'll text it to you now.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

25:48.757 --> 25:53.928
So, in exchange for my help,
maybe you'll buy me a drink?

25:53.928 --> 25:55.680
Well, actually, I'm--

25:55.680 --> 25:58.350
I'm kinda seeing
somebody right now.

25:58.350 --> 26:00.977
Shut up.
Is it serious?

26:00.977 --> 26:04.189
Well, it's a little early,
but it-- it could be, yes.

26:04.189 --> 26:05.940
Well, good luck, stud.

26:05.940 --> 26:08.234
Hey, and if it doesn't work out,
hit me up.

26:08.234 --> 26:10.153
Okay. Alright. Bye.

26:10.153 --> 26:12.447
[ Keyboard clacking ]

26:12.447 --> 26:14.991
Okay, here we are.

26:14.991 --> 26:16.951
Well, it certainly looks
like our mystery woman.

26:16.951 --> 26:18.536
Mm.

26:18.536 --> 26:20.538
She's married to
a Nathan Parker.

26:20.538 --> 26:21.748
Nathan Parker.
I know that name.

26:21.748 --> 26:23.625
He's a--
a big-time developer,

26:23.625 --> 26:26.628
supposedly with ties to
several criminal organizations.

26:26.628 --> 26:27.796
Well, if a man like that thought

26:27.796 --> 26:29.589
that his wife was having
an affair,

26:29.589 --> 26:32.550
it's reasonable to assume that
he would send people after them.

26:32.550 --> 26:33.802
Yeah,
but we still don't know

26:33.802 --> 26:35.136
if Macy and Melinda
were involved.

26:35.136 --> 26:36.304
Hmm.
[ Keyboard clacking ]

26:36.304 --> 26:38.556
Well, her phone pinged
three times

26:38.556 --> 26:40.308
at Macy's clinic
in the last two months.

26:40.308 --> 26:41.768
What about the night
of the accident?

26:41.768 --> 26:42.852
It was off.

26:42.852 --> 26:45.313
Powered back on in her house
in Kailua,

26:45.313 --> 26:46.648
and it hasn't left since.

26:46.648 --> 26:48.608
So she hasn't left her house
in six days?

26:48.608 --> 26:49.984
No, it would seem not.

26:49.984 --> 26:51.903
She hasn't made any calls
or sent any text messages,

26:51.903 --> 26:53.655
and there are no credit
card charges, either.

26:53.655 --> 26:54.989
Okay, here's what I'm thinking, alright?

26:54.989 --> 26:57.075
So, Parker sends his guys
after Melinda,

26:57.075 --> 26:59.244
but they don't get to her
until after the crash

26:59.244 --> 27:00.620
and take her home, or--

27:00.620 --> 27:03.707
Or they disappeared her
and kept her phone.

27:03.707 --> 27:06.418
In which case, we might be
looking at two possible murders.

27:06.418 --> 27:08.044
I think it's time to loop in
Detective Childs.

27:08.044 --> 27:10.046
Yeah, but, look, if the HPD
gets involved now,

27:10.046 --> 27:11.548
Parker's gonna lawyer up.

27:11.548 --> 27:13.133
Maybe we have a better chance
of finding something out

27:13.133 --> 27:14.467
if we talk to him first.

27:14.467 --> 27:16.344
Why is he gonna talk to us?
For the same reason.

27:16.344 --> 27:18.304
He wants to know
what we know.

27:18.304 --> 27:19.848
Hmm.

27:19.848 --> 27:37.615
♪

27:37.615 --> 27:38.658
Hi. Mr. Parker.

27:38.658 --> 27:40.035
My name is Thomas Magnum.

27:40.035 --> 27:41.119
This is Juliet Higgins.

27:41.119 --> 27:42.662
We're private investigators.

27:42.662 --> 27:44.289
How can I help you?

27:44.289 --> 27:46.750
Well, we're looking into
the death of a Dr. Greg Macy.

27:46.750 --> 27:48.209
We have reason to believe
that your wife,

27:48.209 --> 27:50.545
Melinda, may have some
information that could help us.

27:50.545 --> 27:54.090
Would we be able
to speak to her?

27:54.090 --> 27:55.717
Macy?

27:55.717 --> 27:58.303
What, you mean the doctor
who crashed his car last week?

27:58.303 --> 27:59.679
Mm.

27:59.679 --> 28:01.389
Why do you think
Melinda can help you?

28:01.389 --> 28:03.600
Well, we believe
she knew the victim.

28:05.185 --> 28:07.479
[ Sighs ]

28:07.479 --> 28:09.522
I was wondering how long
it would someone

28:09.522 --> 28:10.940
to put that together.

28:12.067 --> 28:14.402
So, you are aware--

28:14.402 --> 28:16.821
That Macy was screwing
my wife? Yeah.

28:16.821 --> 28:18.823
But now isn't the, uh,
best time.

28:18.823 --> 28:20.658
Why don't you leave
your number,

28:20.658 --> 28:22.452
and we'll, uh--
We'll contact you?

28:22.452 --> 28:23.495
Well, it's actually
quite important

28:23.495 --> 28:24.829
that we speak to her now.

28:24.829 --> 28:27.082
We were on our way to HPD
to share our findings

28:27.082 --> 28:30.710
and we need her
to fill in some blanks.

28:35.131 --> 28:36.841
Thanks.

28:39.260 --> 28:42.931
Melinda, this is Mr. Magnum
and Ms. Higgins.

28:42.931 --> 28:45.600
They're
private investigators.

28:45.600 --> 28:47.227
What's this about?

28:47.227 --> 28:49.020
It's about you
and Dr. Macy.

28:49.020 --> 28:51.147
They know,
and they have some questions.

28:51.147 --> 28:54.442
Oh, well, first, actually,
I would like to ask, Mr. Parker,

28:54.442 --> 28:56.778
how you learned
of the affair?

28:56.778 --> 28:58.655
She told me a few days ago.

28:58.655 --> 29:02.117
Sine then, we've just been here, talking,

29:02.117 --> 29:05.120
working on our issues,
working on our marriage.

29:05.120 --> 29:08.123
It's something we should've
done a long time ago.

29:09.916 --> 29:14.212
I gotta say, you do seem
incredibly forgiving

29:14.212 --> 29:15.797
about the whole situation.

29:15.797 --> 29:17.549
Well, um, not at first,

29:17.549 --> 29:19.884
but, no,
the-- the-- the truth is,

29:19.884 --> 29:24.514
what happened was just as much
my fault as it was hers.

29:24.514 --> 29:25.974
I've been so focused on work,

29:25.974 --> 29:29.310
I forgot to invest in the things
that truly matter.

29:29.310 --> 29:35.108
♪

29:35.108 --> 29:39.654
Melinda, what made you
confess to the affair?

29:39.654 --> 29:41.489
I, um...

29:41.489 --> 29:44.200
Well, I saw the news
about Greg's death online

29:44.200 --> 29:45.660
and I was upset.

29:45.660 --> 29:47.078
I could tell something
was wrong,

29:47.078 --> 29:49.998
so finally, I managed
to pull it out of her.

29:51.499 --> 29:52.876
Now I have a question.

29:52.876 --> 29:55.670
Dr. Macy was killed
when he crashed his car.

29:55.670 --> 29:57.672
Seems pretty open and shut.

29:57.672 --> 30:01.051
So, what exactly
are you investigating?

30:01.051 --> 30:05.138
Well, there was an image that
was captured about two minutes

30:05.138 --> 30:09.100
before the crash
that killed Dr. Macy.

30:09.100 --> 30:11.061
That's you inside the car
with him.

30:12.395 --> 30:13.813
That's not me.

30:13.813 --> 30:16.358
It sure does look like you.

30:16.358 --> 30:18.026
It's not. Alright.

30:18.026 --> 30:19.861
Well, in that case,
could I ask you

30:19.861 --> 30:23.198
where you were between 10:30
and 11:00 last Thursday night?

30:23.198 --> 30:25.492
Here, with Nathan.

30:25.492 --> 30:26.868
Well, you gotta admit,

30:26.868 --> 30:31.081
there is a-- a striking
resemblance between you two.

30:33.416 --> 30:34.918
Maybe this guy had a type.

30:36.544 --> 30:38.546
Hmm.

30:38.546 --> 30:41.633
Well, that was something.
Melinda was obviously scared.

30:41.633 --> 30:43.802
Nathan answered
all of her questions,

30:43.802 --> 30:45.345
practically
controlling her.

30:45.345 --> 30:47.138
It just felt very staged.

30:47.138 --> 30:49.224
He probably told her if anyone
comes around asking about

30:49.224 --> 30:52.394
the crash to cop to the affair
so he could avoid suspicion.

30:52.394 --> 30:55.605
Except they weren't counting
on that red light photo

30:55.605 --> 30:56.898
putting her inside the car.

30:56.898 --> 30:58.316
When confronted with that,

30:58.316 --> 31:00.151
her only option was to say
that it wasn't her,

31:00.151 --> 31:02.237
but I reckon
they're hiding something else.

31:02.237 --> 31:03.822
What's that?

31:03.822 --> 31:05.990
Well, Melinda was wearing long
sleeves and really heavy makeup.

31:05.990 --> 31:08.076
Kind of unusual
for a tropical climate.

31:08.076 --> 31:12.205
But it's pretty handy if you're
trying to hide signs of abuse.

31:12.205 --> 31:13.498
I think we've got this
all wrong.

31:13.498 --> 31:15.166
It's not about some affair.

31:20.255 --> 31:21.297
Higgins: According
to the patient records,

31:22.507 --> 31:24.175
there was only one person
who visited the clinic

31:24.175 --> 31:27.178
on the three occasions where
Melinda's phone places her here.

31:27.178 --> 31:28.596
Magnum: Jayne Smith. Come on. Yeah.

31:28.596 --> 31:29.848
That's gotta be an alias.

31:29.848 --> 31:31.516
Same age, height,
and weight as Melinda.

31:31.516 --> 31:34.102
I mean, it's got to be her.

31:34.102 --> 31:36.813
Yeah. [ Sighs ]
You were right.

31:36.813 --> 31:39.274
Parker's been abusing
his wife.

31:39.274 --> 31:40.984
Macy wasn't just
treating her, right?

31:40.984 --> 31:43.737
Those messages to J
we found--

31:43.737 --> 31:45.030
"I-I've been thinking
about you,"

31:45.030 --> 31:46.656
"I can't talk.
He's home."

31:46.656 --> 31:49.284
That wasn't some conversation
between two lovers.

31:49.284 --> 31:51.244
Macy was worried
about Melinda,

31:51.244 --> 31:53.913
and when he looked into
a divorce attorney and housing,

31:53.913 --> 31:55.832
his was probably doing that
on her behalf.

31:55.832 --> 31:58.251
Right. Dr. Macy
wasn't cheating on his wife.

31:58.251 --> 32:01.755
He was just helping Melinda
to leave her abusive husband.

32:01.755 --> 32:03.006
Maybe she finally did.

32:03.006 --> 32:05.216
Only Parker sends guys
after her.

32:05.216 --> 32:07.635
They-- They track her here
to the clinic,

32:07.635 --> 32:10.347
so Macy and Melinda jump in
his car to get away from them.

32:10.347 --> 32:12.015
Then after the crash,
they find Melinda

32:12.015 --> 32:13.433
and take her back home
to her husband,

32:13.433 --> 32:15.477
where he's been
keeping her ever since.

32:15.477 --> 32:16.811
Yeah, it's a solid theory.

32:16.811 --> 32:19.564
Let's just hope our new friend
at HPD believes it.

32:19.564 --> 32:22.233
[ Sighs ]

32:22.233 --> 32:25.236
What did I say
about staying out of this?

32:25.236 --> 32:28.323
Well, we've just told you
that Nathan Parker

32:28.323 --> 32:31.326
is likely responsible
for Dr. Macy's death and appears

32:31.326 --> 32:32.827
to currently be holding
his wife hostage,

32:32.827 --> 32:35.413
a wife who he's been abusing
for God knows how long,

32:35.413 --> 32:37.499
and that is
your first question?

32:37.499 --> 32:39.668
Listen, you go after
a guy like Parker,

32:39.668 --> 32:40.835
you need hard evidence.

32:40.835 --> 32:42.796
You've got location data
and photos

32:42.796 --> 32:45.298
of someone
who could be his wife.

32:45.298 --> 32:47.592
Detective, compare
the birthmarks on the woman

32:47.592 --> 32:49.052
in this photo
to Melinda's.

32:49.052 --> 32:51.179
I guarantee you,
they're gonna match. Alright.

32:51.179 --> 32:52.555
I'll just ask her to come down
here to the station

32:52.555 --> 32:54.599
and get naked for us.
That'll go over so well.

32:54.599 --> 32:57.060
Prosecutors do not like
picking fights they cannot win.

32:57.060 --> 32:59.187
This is a really hard case
to make.

32:59.187 --> 33:01.189
You would need Mrs. Parker
going on the record,

33:01.189 --> 33:03.024
and I've got a better chance
of getting drafted by the A's

33:03.024 --> 33:04.150
than that woman testifying.

33:04.150 --> 33:06.027
So, you're just gonna do nothing,

33:06.027 --> 33:07.570
when every moment
that this woman spends

33:07.570 --> 33:09.239
with her husband,
her life is in danger?

33:09.239 --> 33:10.532
She's also the only person

33:10.532 --> 33:12.325
that can identify
the driver of the SUV

33:12.325 --> 33:14.953
that chased Dr. Macy
to his death.

33:15.912 --> 33:18.707
Thanks for coming in, guys.

33:18.707 --> 33:21.292
Just be grateful I'm not
charging you with obstruction.

33:24.337 --> 33:26.297
We've gotta talk to Melinda
and convince her

33:26.297 --> 33:27.632
to leave her husband
and testify.

33:27.632 --> 33:29.300
How? She's a prisoner
in her own home

33:29.300 --> 33:32.095
surrounded by bodyguards
and completely cut off.

33:32.095 --> 33:33.722
I didn't say it was
gonna be easy.

33:33.722 --> 33:37.892
♪

33:37.892 --> 33:39.352
[ Alarm blaring ]

33:39.352 --> 33:41.229
[ Horn honking ]

33:41.229 --> 33:43.440
[ Blaring continues ]

33:43.440 --> 33:45.150
♪

33:45.150 --> 33:47.027
Turn those alarms off.

33:47.027 --> 33:48.737
[ Blaring continues ]

33:48.737 --> 33:57.579
♪

33:57.579 --> 33:59.581
[ Alarms stop ]

33:59.581 --> 34:24.105
♪

34:24.105 --> 34:25.732
[ Lock disengages ]

34:25.732 --> 34:51.883
♪

34:51.883 --> 34:53.802
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

34:53.802 --> 34:58.139
♪

34:58.139 --> 34:59.933
Go check on Mrs. Parker.

34:59.933 --> 35:11.403
♪

35:11.403 --> 35:13.279
Melinda: You can't be in here.
Higgins: No, no, no.

35:13.279 --> 35:14.656
It's okay.
Your husband isn't home.

35:14.656 --> 35:16.408
We checked.
But he'll be back soon.

35:16.408 --> 35:17.992
You need to go.
I'm going to go,

35:17.992 --> 35:20.161
and you're gonna come
with me, okay?

35:20.161 --> 35:21.871
We know what he's been
doing to you.

35:21.871 --> 35:22.997
No. I can't.

35:22.997 --> 35:26.126
Melinda...
You don't know him.

35:26.126 --> 35:28.294
His men, they ran
Dr. Macy off the road.

35:28.294 --> 35:29.671
No, no. We know.
He'll come after me.

35:29.671 --> 35:31.297
He'll go after my family.
No, no.

35:31.297 --> 35:34.050
We will take him down together.
He won't be able to.

35:34.050 --> 35:35.427
It's not possible.

35:35.427 --> 35:38.388
With the evidence
that we have unearthed

35:38.388 --> 35:40.890
and the testimony
that you can give,

35:40.890 --> 35:45.854
we can put him away
so he will never hurt you again.

35:45.854 --> 35:49.482
Melinda, if you stay with him
in this house, he will kill you.

35:49.482 --> 35:50.900
Maybe not the next time
he hits you,

35:50.900 --> 35:55.280
maybe not the time after that,
but it will happen.

35:55.280 --> 36:00.577
Dr. Macy, he understood
the danger that you were in.

36:00.577 --> 36:03.038
He gave his life
trying to save yours.

36:03.038 --> 36:05.498
♪

36:05.498 --> 36:06.875
Okay.

36:06.875 --> 36:08.668
♪

36:08.668 --> 36:09.878
Let's go.

36:09.878 --> 36:16.885
♪

36:16.885 --> 36:18.428
Come on.

36:18.428 --> 36:26.770
♪

36:26.770 --> 36:27.937
Go.
Get out of here.

36:27.937 --> 36:39.699
♪

36:39.699 --> 36:41.493
[ Gun cocks ]

36:41.493 --> 36:43.536
Where do you think
you're going?

36:43.536 --> 36:44.662
♪

36:49.292 --> 36:51.419
That's close enough.

36:51.419 --> 36:52.420
So, what now?

36:52.420 --> 36:55.090
You gonna call HPD?

36:55.090 --> 36:58.259
You've been holding
your wife hostage in this house.

36:58.259 --> 36:59.636
How are
you gonna explain that?

36:59.636 --> 37:03.515
Lucky for me,
I won't have to.

37:03.515 --> 37:05.433
'Cause we're gonna keep HPD
out of this.

37:05.433 --> 37:08.061
[ Sirens wailing ]

37:08.061 --> 37:13.274
♪

37:13.274 --> 37:15.735
[ Panting ]

37:15.735 --> 37:17.946
Did you call the police?
No.

37:17.946 --> 37:19.030
Well, then how did they--

37:19.030 --> 37:20.782
I have no idea.

37:20.782 --> 37:30.000
♪

37:30.000 --> 37:32.293
[ Indistinct conversations ]

37:32.293 --> 37:35.296
♪

37:35.296 --> 37:36.923
Yeah, so make sure
they know that.

37:36.923 --> 37:39.217
Yeah. Copy.
I'm heading over now.

37:39.217 --> 37:40.760
If nobody called HPD,

37:40.760 --> 37:43.972
then how did you know
to come down with the cavalry?

37:43.972 --> 37:45.682
After what I said about
needing testimony

37:45.682 --> 37:47.475
from Melinda
and your reaction to it,

37:47.475 --> 37:51.354
I just had a feeling
this might be your next move.

37:51.354 --> 37:53.648
He had a feeling.

37:53.648 --> 37:56.943
Between us,
this is what you planned.

37:56.943 --> 37:58.737
You provoked us
into coming here

37:58.737 --> 38:01.740
because you didn't have the
legal grounds to do it yourself.

38:01.740 --> 38:04.492
♪

38:04.492 --> 38:06.327
You two have a good night.

38:06.327 --> 38:19.841
♪

38:19.841 --> 38:27.015
♪ I found a letter that read ♪

38:27.015 --> 38:31.770
♪

38:31.770 --> 38:34.731
I didn't want your husband
involved, but...

38:34.731 --> 38:37.484
He wouldn't listen, right?

38:37.484 --> 38:40.403
[ Sniffles ]

38:40.403 --> 38:42.739
That's who he was.

38:43.907 --> 38:45.950
♪ I think it's coming ♪

38:45.950 --> 38:52.457
♪ Oh, and it comes so fast ♪

38:52.457 --> 38:53.750
I owe him my life.

38:53.750 --> 38:56.795
♪ I'm hearing whispers ♪

38:56.795 --> 39:02.592
♪ Of an infinite yes ♪

39:02.592 --> 39:05.553
♪ And I don't know why it is ♪

39:05.553 --> 39:08.181
♪ Our bodies are dead ♪

39:08.181 --> 39:12.227
♪ Why you look so sad ♪
[ Cellphone beeps ]

39:12.227 --> 39:14.562
It's Gordon Katsumoto.

39:14.562 --> 39:16.940
Listen, I changed my mind.

39:16.940 --> 39:20.026
I'm not gonna let them
take my badge without a fight.

39:21.528 --> 39:24.239
♪ And I don't know why it is ♪

39:24.239 --> 39:26.616
♪ I feel it coming ♪
[ Cellphone chimes ]

39:26.616 --> 39:29.994
♪ I think it's real
and significant ♪

39:29.994 --> 39:34.833
♪ I think I think I think
a little too often ♪

39:34.833 --> 39:37.836
♪ That's what
my therapist said ♪

39:37.836 --> 39:40.588
♪ We're alone
in this wilderness ♪

39:40.588 --> 39:43.049
♪ Left to choke on the pills ♪

39:43.049 --> 39:46.219
♪ And to feed on the viruses ♪

39:46.219 --> 39:47.929
♪ I think it's coming ♪

39:47.929 --> 39:51.599
♪ Oh, and it comes so ♪

39:51.599 --> 39:53.101
♪ Fast ♪

39:53.101 --> 39:55.103
What is this?

39:55.103 --> 39:59.524
I was thinking about
what you said, and you're right.

40:01.401 --> 40:04.279
We did skip a few steps.

40:04.279 --> 40:06.614
Now is a good time to start
making up for that.

40:06.614 --> 40:09.242
That is very sweet.

40:09.242 --> 40:15.749
♪

40:15.749 --> 40:20.128
Kumu is, uh, picking up
a shift at La Mariana,

40:20.128 --> 40:24.299
which means we have
the entire estate

40:24.299 --> 40:26.301
all to ourselves.

40:26.301 --> 40:29.137
Magnum, that--
That's a vintage Bordeaux.

40:29.137 --> 40:31.639
Do you have any idea
how expensive that is?

40:31.639 --> 40:34.476
Well, you're worth
every penny,

40:34.476 --> 40:36.144
even if it's not mine.

40:39.189 --> 40:40.482
Don't ruin it.

40:40.482 --> 40:42.275
Sorry.

40:45.111 --> 40:46.363
Cheers.

40:46.363 --> 40:55.455
♪

40:55.455 --> 40:56.706
Excuse me.

40:56.706 --> 40:58.124
Are you the harbor master?

40:58.124 --> 40:59.584
That's me.

40:59.584 --> 41:00.877
I'm looking for a friend
of mine.

41:00.877 --> 41:03.546
I believe he docks
his boat here.

41:03.546 --> 41:04.673
Yeah.

41:04.673 --> 41:05.715
His boat was here
this morning.

41:05.715 --> 41:07.175
Really?
Yeah.

41:07.175 --> 41:08.218
But the slip's empty.

41:08.218 --> 41:09.761
So your friend
must have set sail.

41:09.761 --> 41:12.055
Would you happen to have
the boat's MMSI number?

41:12.055 --> 41:13.932
I would love to track it
if I can.

41:13.932 --> 41:15.725
Sorry. I'm just
the harbor master.

41:15.725 --> 41:18.269
I don't keep that kind
of information on file.

41:18.269 --> 41:19.312
It's okay.

41:19.312 --> 41:20.397
Mahalo.

41:20.397 --> 41:30.740
♪

41:30.740 --> 41:32.367
You asked me to call
if somebody came around

41:32.367 --> 41:34.452
asking about the Navy guy.

41:34.452 --> 41:35.870
Someone just did.

41:35.870 --> 41:36.913
Who?

41:36.913 --> 41:39.082
Don't know.
Said he was a friend.

41:39.082 --> 41:40.625
I didn't get a name.

41:40.625 --> 41:42.210
He comes back, you call me.

41:42.210 --> 41:45.046
Problem?

41:45.046 --> 41:46.214
Not sure yet.

41:46.214 --> 41:48.049
Is he up?
Yeah.

41:48.049 --> 41:59.436
♪

41:59.436 --> 42:00.603
Who are you?

42:00.603 --> 42:02.522
That's not important, Captain.

42:02.522 --> 42:03.857
I'm not a captain anymore.

42:03.857 --> 42:05.650
No, but you were.
Four decades in the Navy.

42:05.650 --> 42:07.193
Served with distinction.

42:07.193 --> 42:08.862
Highly decorated.

42:08.862 --> 42:12.532
And, of course, resigned
your commission in disgrace.

42:12.532 --> 42:13.908
Thanks for the recap.

42:13.908 --> 42:15.744
You've obviously done
your homework on me.

42:15.744 --> 42:17.203
Now, what the hell
is this about?!

42:17.203 --> 42:18.288
Easy.

42:18.288 --> 42:19.998
You're telling <i>me</i>
to take it easy?

42:19.998 --> 42:22.584
You break into my home,
black bag me, knock me out.

42:22.584 --> 42:24.085
Now, what do you want?

42:24.085 --> 42:25.253
Information.

42:26.921 --> 42:29.924
Back in Afghanistan,
you put together a team.

42:29.924 --> 42:32.761
Two Navy SEALs, two Marines.

42:32.761 --> 42:35.096
They ran black ops.
Off-the-books stuff.

42:35.096 --> 42:38.391
Their identities were known
only to you and a few others.

42:41.686 --> 42:43.646
You're gonna give me
their names.

42:45.648 --> 42:47.776
Why the hell
would I do that?

42:47.776 --> 42:51.696
So we can hunt them down
and kill them.

42:51.696 --> 42:53.031
♪
